The paper analyzes the research output of the Networked Knowledge Organization Systems (NKOS) community, which is concerned with organizing and managing digital information. This falls under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Digital Libraries (cs.DL). The paper also uses network analysis to study the co-authorship network of the community, which can be categorized under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Social Computing (cs.SOC). Lastly, the paper investigates gender differences in collaboration behavior, which can be related to Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HCI).
